comment: hepatocellular carcinoma -> carcinoma of liver and intrahepatic biliary tract
follicular lymphoma (non-Hodgkins) -> Hodgkins lymphoma (MS4A1 involved in both)
infection -> Recurrent infection due to specific granule deficiency
Blast Phase Chronic Myelogenous Leukemia; BCR-ABL1 Positive -> chronic myelogenous leukemia
von Hippel-Lindau disease -> renal cell carcinoma
familial intrahepatic cholestasis -> serum metabolite measurement
achondroplasia -> Tall stature - scoliosis - macrodactyly of the great toes
homozygous familial hypercholesterolemia -> low density lipoprotein cholesterol measurement
diffuse large b-cell lymphoma -> B-cell non-Hodgkins lymphoma
NMOSD -> autoimmune disorder of central nervous system
HER2 negative breast carcinoma -> breast carcinoma
Tenosynovial Giant Cell Tumor -> giant cell tumor (parent)
acquired thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura -> thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura (parent)
hepatic veno-occlusive disease -> hepatic vascular disorder (parent)
primary biliary cirrhosis -> cirrhosis of liver (parent)
precursor B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia -> B-cell non-Hodgkins lymphoma
type 2 diabetes mellitus -> Disorder of carbohydrate metabolism
